name: sfchronicle
text:
A lockdown order that takes effect in Lake Tahoe today and extends through Jan. 1 casts doubt over many families’ holiday travel plans and thrown the region’s lodging industry into upheaval.
https://t.co/MLiHqNTQnw

name: sfchronicle
text:
The U.S. Supreme Court rejected a bid to overturn election results in swing states that voted for President-elect Joe Biden, a long-shot effort that was backed by key California GOP figures.

https://t.co/HmA3y2JHxa

name: sfchronicle
text:
Henry Schulman, who has covered the @SFGiants for the past three and a half decades, including 23 seasons for @sfchronicle, is leaving the paper and retiring from daily journalism. 

He explains why: https://t.co/glPSbPw6vW

name: sfchronicle
text:
The Cardinal, or his “traveling band” as head coach David Shaw calls them, seem to be bonding in an us-against-the-world situation that forced them to move the team to Seattle last week and use 10 buses to relocate the program to Oregon this week.
https://t.co/ebsltzz7Nv
